  "2026-05-11T20:21:18.026Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: ran pm context --limit 10, pm search package architecture external packages SDK extension core complexity --limit 10, pm search core boundary barebone package externalize custom commands --limit 10, pm list-open --limit 20, and pm list-in-progress --limit 20. Existing active match is pm-59gj; no child item specifically tracks the core-boundary migration matrix."
  "2026-05-11T21:16:54.699Z",codex-agent,"Boundary matrix completed for first implementation slice: core keeps item lifecycle/storage/history/locks/settings/contracts/package loader/output/minimal health; optional customizations start moving into installable packages, with Beads/Todos extracted first and telemetry/Sentry/search/calendar left as later package-boundary work because they cross broader runtime contracts."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-11T20:32:39.121Z",codex-agent,"Core boundary classification from codebase explorers: keep item lifecycle/storage, durable logs, package loader/governance, contracts, output, history, lock, settings, and minimal health in core. Move import/export bridges first, then templates and semantic providers/vector stores; split calendar only after context has a small agenda primitive; move telemetry/Sentry last because it crosses startup, parse errors, privacy, and release gates."
